translated_text: [[How do I know if it's a Gludinhorn?|HowHorn]]

original_text: [[Yes, and Clancy is excellent at his job.|BodyDog]]
translated_text: [[Yes, and Clancy is excellent at his job.|BodyDog]]

original_text: Adina: We didn't anticipate that you would have this combination of snowmen.
translated_text: Adina: We didn't anticipate that you would have this combination of snowmen.

original_text: Adina: So... uh... sorry about that?
translated_text: Adina: So... uh... sorry about that?

original_text: Adina: I'm not sure if this is really helpful, but ok.
translated_text: Adina: I'm not sure if this is really helpful, but ok.

original_text: Adina: Your collar said "Clancy". Is that your name?
translated_text: Adina: Your collar said "Clancy". Is that your name?

original_text: Adina: I hope you don't screw this up for me, Clancy!
translated_text: Adina: I hope you don't screw this up for me, Clancy!

original_text: Adina: But I hope soon you'll be able to move on
translated_text: Adina: But I hope soon you'll be able to move on

original_text: Adina: to wherever dead dogs go.
translated_text: Adina: to wherever dead dogs go.

original_text: Adina: Ok boy, follow my lead!
translated_text: Adina: Ok boy, follow my lead!

original_text: Snowthief: Ugh. What do you want?
translated_text: Snowthief: Ugh. What do you want?

original_text: Adina: Sorry to bother you, but I need your help.
translated_text: Adina: Sorry to bother you, but I need your help.

original_text: Snowthief: Oh crap. I died, didn't I?
translated_text: Snowthief: Oh crap. I died, didn't I?

original_text: Adina: Listen, by me bringing you here
translated_text: Adina: Listen, by me bringing you here

original_text: Adina: I think you'll be able to get out of these woods
translated_text: Adina: I think you'll be able to get out of these woods

original_text: Adina: and do whatever dead people do.
translated_text: Adina: and do whatever dead people do.

original_text: Snowthief: Is that something I want?
translated_text: Snowthief: Is that something I want?

original_text: Adina: Ok wow, are you just a horn?
translated_text: Adina: Ok wow, are you just a horn?

original_text: Adina: Let's try this- honk once for yes and twice for no. Got it?
translated_text: Adina: Let's try this- honk once for yes and twice for no. Got it?

original_text: Adina: Are you just a horn ghost kind of thing?
translated_text: Adina: Are you just a horn ghost kind of thing?

original_text: Adina: Are you the person who played this horn?
translated_text: Adina: Are you the person who played this horn?

original_text: Adina: Listen, by bringing you back
translated_text: Adina: Listen, by bringing you back

original_text: Adina: I think you'll be able to get out of these woods
translated_text: Adina: I think you'll be able to get out of these woods

original_text: Adina: and do whatever dead people do.
translated_text: Adina: and do whatever dead people do.

original_text: Adina: Ok, great! Follow my lead.
translated_text: Adina: Ok, great! Follow my lead.

original_text: Snowdrunk: I can't believe I've been sober the entire time I've been dead.
translated_text: Snowdrunk: I can't believe I've been sober the entire time I've been dead.

original_text: Snowdrunk: Let's do this. I'm not getting any less dead.
translated_text: Snowdrunk: Let's do this. I'm not getting any less dead.

original_text: Adina: Sorry to be abrupt, but I need your help.
translated_text: Adina: Sorry to be abrupt, but I need your help.

original_text: Adina: You're on the Forest God's mountain.
translated_text: Adina: You're on the Forest God's mountain.

original_text: Snowdunk: Oh! Are we going to see the Forest God?
translated_text: Snowdunk: Oh! Are we going to see the Forest God?

original_text: Snowdrunk: Because I'm going to the Frozen Lake.
translated_text: Snowdrunk: Because I'm going to the Frozen Lake.

original_text: Adina: Listen, by my bringing you here
translated_text: Adina: Listen, by my bringing you here

original_text: Adina: I think you'll be able to get out of these woods
translated_text: Adina: I think you'll be able to get out of these woods

original_text: Adina: and do whatever dead people do.
translated_text: Adina: and do whatever dead people do.

original_text: Snowdrunk: Ok, that sounds as likely as anything else that's happening.
translated_text: Snowdrunk: Ok, that sounds as likely as anything else that's happening.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Oh Empress, the Forest God is still ill.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Oh Empress, the Forest God is still ill.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: If only I just knew why, and whether they would be well again.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: If only I just knew why, and whether they would be well again.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: I thank you for leaving your companions with me, as they have been a great comfort.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: I thank you for leaving your companions with me, as they have been a great comfort.

original_text: Adina: No problem. I entrust them to your care.
translated_text: Adina: No problem. I entrust them to your care.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Empress! It's so late! Why are you still here?
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Empress! It's so late! Why are you still here?

original_text: Adina: Listen, this is very important.
translated_text: Adina: Listen, this is very important.

original_text: Adina: I know why your god is dying.
translated_text: Adina: I know why your god is dying.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: No, you must tell it to them.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: No, you must tell it to them.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: I'm not worthy of hearing of their weaknesses.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: I'm not worthy of hearing of their weaknesses.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: I don't deserve the peace I have found here
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: I don't deserve the peace I have found here

original_text: GodtenderBrown: and I must honor them as best as my frail self will allow.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: and I must honor them as best as my frail self will allow.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: This is the worst Longest Night ever.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: This is the worst Longest Night ever.

original_text: Adina: How can a god be sick?
translated_text: Adina: How can a god be sick?

original_text: GodtenderBrown: [shake=.02]If only I knew what was happening!!!![/shake]
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: [shake=.02]If only I knew what was happening!!!![/shake]

original_text: GodtenderBrown: We Godtenders are tasked with caring for the Forest God.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: We Godtenders are tasked with caring for the Forest God.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: But this sickness, we have never seen its like.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: But this sickness, we have never seen its like.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Not in the 700 years of records kept since Saint Cecil began Tending God.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Not in the 700 years of records kept since Saint Cecil began Tending God.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: We thought when the peace came, all would be well.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: We thought when the peace came, all would be well.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: But centuries of conflict with her have weakened them.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: But centuries of conflict with her have weakened them.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: And not long after they became ill.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: And not long after they became ill.

original_text: GodtenderBrown:{angryWobble=5} DO NOT SAY HER NAME HERE.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown:{angryWobble=5} DO NOT SAY HER NAME HERE.

original_text: GodtenderBrown:{angryWobble=0} My heart is broken. My god is sick and old.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown:{angryWobble=0} My heart is broken. My god is sick and old.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: I don't know what my life would be without them.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: I don't know what my life would be without them.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: There is nothing you can do, Empress.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: There is nothing you can do, Empress.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: As representative of the Forest Throne,
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: As representative of the Forest Throne,

original_text: GodtenderBrown: I say that no power of the Forest God shall bar your way this Longest Night.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: I say that no power of the Forest God shall bar your way this Longest Night.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: As for [speed=.5][shake=.01]Her[/all], you are at the mercy
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: As for [speed=.5][shake=.01]Her[/all], you are at the mercy

original_text: GodtenderBrown: of the most dangerous creature in the forest.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: of the most dangerous creature in the forest.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Go, and take a blessing with you.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Go, and take a blessing with you.

original_text: Adina: How can a god be dying?

original_text: GodtenderBrown: I do not pretend to know the ways of such things.

translated_text: GodtenderBrown: We Godtenders are tasked with caring for the Forest God.

original_text: Adina: When Clancy was but a child
translated_text: Adina: When Clancy was but a child

original_text: Adina: He longed to bring peace to the beasts of the field.
translated_text: Adina: He longed to bring peace to the beasts of the field.

original_text: Adina: And he was blessed with the ability to speak to them.
translated_text: Adina: And he was blessed with the ability to speak to them.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Why does he not speak to us?
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Why does he not speak to us?

original_text: [[He has forgotten how, such is his dedication.|FGForgotten]]
translated_text: [[He has forgotten how, such is his dedication.|FGForgotten]]

original_text: [[He is currently speaking to our Imperial Hound, Dart.|FGDart]]
translated_text: [[He is currently speaking to our Imperial Hound, Dart.|FGDart]]

original_text: Snowdrunk: Yes, this dog has a straight line through to heaven.
translated_text: Snowdrunk: Yes, this dog has a straight line through to heaven.

original_text: Adina: He was born with one ear that was white as the snow
translated_text: Adina: He was born with one ear that was white as the snow

original_text: Adina: and that's the ear he uses to hear the celestial realms.
translated_text: Adina: and that's the ear he uses to hear the celestial realms.

original_text: Snowdrunk: dear god either shut that dog up or send me back to death
translated_text: Snowdrunk: dear god either shut that dog up or send me back to death

original_text: [[Clancy is receiving a vision right this moment!|FGVision]]
translated_text: [[Clancy is receiving a vision right this moment!|FGVision]]

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Oh, you have a dog with you as well! I love dogs!
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Oh, you have a dog with you as well! I love dogs!

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Yes Archbishop Clancy, I wish to speak with your dog!
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Yes Archbishop Clancy, I wish to speak with your dog!

original_text: Adina: Williams! Perhaps you could... ask Dart to speak?
translated_text: Adina: Williams! Perhaps you could... ask Dart to speak?

original_text: GodtenderBrown: And yet I hear the weight of many gin-soaked years in him.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: And yet I hear the weight of many gin-soaked years in him.

original_text: Adina: Clancy is helping poor Dart turn his life around!
translated_text: Adina: Clancy is helping poor Dart turn his life around!

original_text: Snowdrunk: I hate all of you.
translated_text: Snowdrunk: I hate all of you.

original_text: Adina: The air is very cold, may we pass through?
translated_text: Adina: The air is very cold, may we pass through?

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Anyone with such a good-hearted, virtuous Archbishop
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Anyone with such a good-hearted, virtuous Archbishop

original_text: GodtenderBrown: and a dog of such moral fortitude and bravery
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: and a dog of such moral fortitude and bravery

original_text: GodtenderBrown: must be worthy of inspection by the Forest God.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: must be worthy of inspection by the Forest God.

original_text: Adina: He is a candidate for sainthood, where we come from.
translated_text: Adina: He is a candidate for sainthood, where we come from.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Beatification, while he yet lives?
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Beatification, while he yet lives?

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Who ever has heard of such a thing?
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Who ever has heard of such a thing?

original_text: Adina: He's the secret son of the king.
translated_text: Adina: He's the secret son of the king.

original_text: Adina: So he's being fast-tracked to sainthood.
translated_text: Adina: So he's being fast-tracked to sainthood.

original_text: Adina: Hey, you don't have to convince me!
translated_text: Adina: Hey, you don't have to convince me!

original_text: Snowdrunk: But it's not his fault.
translated_text: Snowdrunk: But it's not his fault.

original_text: Adina: He's just a nice, sweet guy
translated_text: Adina: He's just a nice, sweet guy

original_text: Snowdrunk: This was a good idea.
translated_text: Snowdrunk: This was a good idea.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Your dedication to this one barking holy man in your empire
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Your dedication to this one barking holy man in your empire

original_text: GodtenderBrown: has convinced me that your heart is reverent and pure.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: has convinced me that your heart is reverent and pure.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: I'm sorry, but this is too spooky for me.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: I'm sorry, but this is too spooky for me.

original_text: Adina: Godtender Brown, are you there?
translated_text: Adina: Godtender Brown, are you there?

original_text: Adina: Are you afraid of one little saintly ghost?
translated_text: Adina: Are you afraid of one little saintly ghost?

original_text: Adina: Oh, won't you come back and let us through?
translated_text: Adina: Oh, won't you come back and let us through?

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Can you promise me that your ghost will not spook me?
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Can you promise me that your ghost will not spook me?

original_text: Adina: What do you think, Williams?
translated_text: Adina: What do you think, Williams?

original_text: Snowdrunk: I believe we can do it, Empress!
translated_text: Snowdrunk: I believe we can do it, Empress!

original_text: GodtenderBrown: I will let you pass, on the condition that no one gets spooked.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: I will let you pass, on the condition that no one gets spooked.

original_text: Snowdrunk: The Archbishop has spoken a blessing upon you
translated_text: Snowdrunk: The Archbishop has spoken a blessing upon you

original_text: Snowdrunk: for allowing the Empress an audience with the Forest God.
translated_text: Snowdrunk: for allowing the Empress an audience with the Forest God.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: But I haven't let you pass yet!
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: But I haven't let you pass yet!

original_text: Adina: Yes, but the Archbishop is possessed of forsight!
translated_text: Adina: Yes, but the Archbishop is possessed of forsight!

original_text: GodtenderBrown: But how does he know the future is certain?
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: But how does he know the future is certain?

original_text: Adina: He sees all possibilities and knows which one shall be!
translated_text: Adina: He sees all possibilities and knows which one shall be!

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Do I really have a choice then?
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Do I really have a choice then?

original_text: Adina: No, it is fated that you shall let us pass.
translated_text: Adina: No, it is fated that you shall let us pass.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: I feel now like whatever happens is inevitable.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: I feel now like whatever happens is inevitable.

original_text: Adina: But you got a blessing out of it!
translated_text: Adina: But you got a blessing out of it!

original_text: GodtenderBrown: I hope the blessing will help me to understand this troubling idea.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: I hope the blessing will help me to understand this troubling idea.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: The intuitiveness of your companions has convinced me that you are worthy to pass.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: The intuitiveness of your companions has convinced me that you are worthy to pass.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Archbishop Clancy, tell us what things you see!
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Archbishop Clancy, tell us what things you see!

original_text: Snowdrunk: My limited skills can no longer translate.
translated_text: Snowdrunk: My limited skills can no longer translate.

original_text: Adina: We must consign such wonders to the beasts.
translated_text: Adina: We must consign such wonders to the beasts.

original_text: Adina: The badgers. The stoats. The titmice. The bear-children.
translated_text: Adina: The badgers. The stoats. The titmice. The bear-children.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: We witnessed a miracle, on Longest Night no less.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: We witnessed a miracle, on Longest Night no less.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: You are most blessed, Empress.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: You are most blessed, Empress.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: You may pass, and I ask that you leave some of that blessing here.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: You may pass, and I ask that you leave some of that blessing here.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Remarkable! There are other forests like this one?
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Remarkable! There are other forests like this one?

original_text: Adina: Well, not exactly like this...
translated_text: Adina: Well, not exactly like this...

original_text: Adina: Yes. It would be hard to call it a forest if there weren't trees.
translated_text: Adina: Yes. It would be hard to call it a forest if there weren't trees.

original_text: Snowthief: I seen a man drowned.
translated_text: Snowthief: I seen a man drowned.

original_text: Snowthief: The seaweed grabbed 'im like hair from a drowned ghost.
translated_text: Snowthief: The seaweed grabbed 'im like hair from a drowned ghost.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Oooh! I'm good and spooked now!
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Oooh! I'm good and spooked now!

original_text: [[We have traveled long, past many an ocean-ghost.|GhostOcean]]
translated_text: [[We have traveled long, past many an ocean-ghost.|GhostOcean]]

original_text: [[Listen, that kind of thing doesn't exist.|DoesntExist]]
translated_text: [[Listen, that kind of thing doesn't exist.|DoesntExist]]

original_text: GodtenderBrown: My father was from over the western ocean.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: My father was from over the western ocean.

original_text: SnowThief: So am I! Small world.
translated_text: SnowThief: So am I! Small world.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: I thought I recognized that voice.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: I thought I recognized that voice.

original_text: Adina: No, he's not your father.
translated_text: Adina: No, he's not your father.

original_text: [[Uh, Archbishop Williams, will you council this confused man?|HelpDad]]
translated_text: [[Uh, Archbishop Williams, will you council this confused man?|HelpDad]]

original_text: SnowThief: You're saying seaweed don't exist?
translated_text: SnowThief: You're saying seaweed don't exist?

original_text: Adina: Yes, obviously that was what I was saying.
translated_text: Adina: Yes, obviously that was what I was saying.

original_text: SnowThief: Well ok then, you're the expert on what exists.
translated_text: SnowThief: Well ok then, you're the expert on what exists.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: I'm sorry, but we do not allow sarcasm on the Holy Mountain.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: I'm sorry, but we do not allow sarcasm on the Holy Mountain.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: What a cynical empire you must hail from.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: What a cynical empire you must hail from.

original_text: Adina: Listen, if we lay down our sarcasm, our cynicism, our irony
translated_text: Adina: Listen, if we lay down our sarcasm, our cynicism, our irony

original_text: Adina: may we cross over to see the Forest God?
translated_text: Adina: may we cross over to see the Forest God?

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Bring not one word of insincerity here!
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Bring not one word of insincerity here!

original_text: GodtenderBrown: And you may pass. But watch yourself.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: And you may pass. But watch yourself.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: I am afraid of ghosts
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: I am afraid of ghosts

original_text: GodtenderBrown: and horses, but I feel that's not relevant here.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: and horses, but I feel that's not relevant here.

original_text: Adina: Fair enough. Those are all scary things.
translated_text: Adina: Fair enough. Those are all scary things.

translated_text: GodtenderBrown: And the demon entered his broken body

translated_text: GodtenderBrown: until he was driven out by Saint Balfa and the Charmed Goat.

translated_text: [[What does all of this do for you?|DoForYou]]

translated_text: Adina: I wonder if there's a head in there?

translated_text: Mae: If I ever find a body part on the ground

translated_text: Mae: I am gonna poke it with a stick.

translated_text: Snowdrunk: Thanks for helping me get out of here.

translated_text: Adina: How did you end up here, anyway?

translated_text: Snowdrunk: The frozen lake was east.

translated_text: Snowdrunk: And then I was dead too.

translated_text: Snowdrunk: Kinda nice up here. Peaceful.

translated_text: Adina: Oh, you're already gone, huh?

translated_text: Adina: I hope you're going someplace better.

translated_text: Snowthief: I was an exceptional thief.

translated_text: Adina: How did you end up in the forest?

original_text: Snowthief: I was going to rob the Huncher.
translated_text: Snowthief: I was going to rob the Huncher.

original_text: Snowthief: She's got to have loads of priceless crap.
translated_text: Snowthief: She's got to have loads of priceless crap.

original_text: Snowthief: I remember reaching up, trying to grab the sun
translated_text: Snowthief: I remember reaching up, trying to grab the sun

original_text: Snowthief: as the snow covered me.
translated_text: Snowthief: as the snow covered me.

original_text: Snowthief: You do dumb half-asleep things when you die.
translated_text: Snowthief: You do dumb half-asleep things when you die.

original_text: Snowthief: There's your deep insight on the dying process.
translated_text: Snowthief: There's your deep insight on the dying process.

translated_text: Snowthief: It was a lock and a key. Only one set like them.

translated_text: Adina: i never said- thanks for the arm.

translated_text: GodtenderBrown: The blessing of the Forest God goes with you.

original_text: Adina: Sorry, is that a weird question?
translated_text: Adina: Sorry, is that a weird question?

original_text: GodtenderBrown: I think it gives me a truth I can't find anywhere else.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: I think it gives me a truth I can't find anywhere else.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: And one I have to find every day when I wake up.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: And one I have to find every day when I wake up.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: Like, it's there, but I don't have a map to it.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: Like, it's there, but I don't have a map to it.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: and looking for it is where I find everything else.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: and looking for it is where I find everything else.

translated_text: Adina: Wait, but isn't the Forest God in there right now?

original_text: Adina: Where is the mystery in what you're looking for?
translated_text: Adina: Where is the mystery in what you're looking for?

original_text: GodtenderBrown: The Forest God does not behave as I always expect
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: The Forest God does not behave as I always expect

original_text: GodtenderBrown: and the difference between my expectations and reality
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: and the difference between my expectations and reality

original_text: GodtenderBrown: I can only hope that the Forest God may heal.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: I can only hope that the Forest God may heal.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: ha ha ha ha ha!
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: ha ha ha ha ha!

original_text: GodtenderBrown: I am from the country of giants!
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: I am from the country of giants!

original_text: GodtenderBrown: I am wearing the thickest of coats
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: I am wearing the thickest of coats

original_text: GodtenderBrown: and the warmest of our Godtender hats.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: and the warmest of our Godtender hats.

original_text: GodtenderBrown: there isn't a chill frosty enough to touch these bones.
translated_text: GodtenderBrown: there isn't a chill frosty enough to touch these bones.

translated_text: Mae: And then she jumped over the kazm!

original_text: Granddad: It's "chasm," and no she didn't.
translated_text: Granddad: It's "chasm," and no she didn't.

original_text: Granddad: The gap was too wide. She would have never made it.
translated_text: Granddad: The gap was too wide. She would have never made it.

original_text: Granddad: That's not how it happened.
translated_text: Granddad: That's not how it happened.

translated_text: Mae: She was an expert ski jumper. She could have made it across easily!

original_text: Granddad: She wasn't. They didn't have skiing back then.
translated_text: Granddad: She wasn't. They didn't have skiing back then.

original_text: Mae: She jumped across with her slidey-snowshoes!
translated_text: Mae: She jumped across with her slidey-snowshoes!

original_text: Granddad: No, the gap was too wide.
translated_text: Granddad: No, the gap was too wide.

original_text: Mae: No it wasn't! I can see it.
translated_text: Mae: No it wasn't! I can see it.

original_text: Granddad: Well I can see it too and it's my story.
translated_text: Granddad: Well I can see it too and it's my story.

original_text: Mae: If you can say she couldn't I can say she could!
translated_text: Mae: If you can say she couldn't I can say she could!

original_text: Mae: She jumped because it's my story now!
translated_text: Mae: She jumped because it's my story now!

original_text: Granddad: Ok then. She jumped across
translated_text: Granddad: Ok then. She jumped across

original_text: Granddad: and I don't know what happened after that.
translated_text: Granddad: and I don't know what happened after that.

original_text: Granddad: I thought it was your story now?
translated_text: Granddad: I thought it was your story now?

original_text: Granddad: Maybe the story is both of ours?
translated_text: Granddad: Maybe the story is both of ours?

original_text: Granddad: How about we work together?
translated_text: Granddad: How about we work together?

original_text: Granddad: So anyway, she couldn't jump over the cliff...
translated_text: Granddad: So anyway, she couldn't jump over the cliff...

original_text: Mae: And then... oh right. She didn't jump.
translated_text: Mae: And then... oh right. She didn't jump.

original_text: HuncherOutside: Who's that walking on my porch?
translated_text: HuncherOutside: Who's that walking on my porch?

original_text: HuncherOutside: Oh girl, it's all over now.
translated_text: HuncherOutside: Oh girl, it's all over now.

original_text: HuncherInside: There are old bodies in the north.
translated_text: HuncherInside: There are old bodies in the north.

original_text: HuncherInside: Where the ground never thaws.
translated_text: HuncherInside: Where the ground never thaws.

original_text: HuncherInside: Frozen in the dirt and ice for millenia.
translated_text: HuncherInside: Frozen in the dirt and ice for millenia.

original_text: HuncherInside: In some of them there is a sickness against which we are no longer strong.
translated_text: HuncherInside: In some of them there is a sickness against which we are no longer strong.

original_text: HuncherInside: Someday the earth will warm, and the ice will melt.
translated_text: HuncherInside: Someday the earth will warm, and the ice will melt.

original_text: HuncherInside: And that sickness will finish the work on us
translated_text: HuncherInside: And that sickness will finish the work on us

original_text: HuncherInside: that began when we were first born.
translated_text: HuncherInside: that began when we were first born.

original_text: HuncherInside: [shake=.02]KID! Will you please stop that honking?[/shake]
translated_text: HuncherInside: [shake=.02]KID! Will you please stop that honking?[/shake]

original_text: HuncherInside: I'm going to leave you where they'll never find you.
translated_text: HuncherInside: I'm going to leave you where they'll never find you.

translated_text: [[I need to get to the Frozen Lake.|NeedFrozenLake]]

translated_text: Adina: I can't move. This hurts. Stop.

translated_text: Adina: I need somewhere to hide!

translated_text: HuncherOutside: Damn Squirrels won't take a break.

translated_text: HuncherOutside: North wind, black wind, wolf in the dark!

original_text: HuncherOutside: Ugh, this weather never behaves.
translated_text: HuncherOutside: Ugh, this weather never behaves.

original_text: HuncherOutside: Gotta say the whole damn thing every time.
translated_text: HuncherOutside: Gotta say the whole damn thing every time.

translated_text: HuncherOutside: Blue fire in the north! I have discovered your secret name!

original_text: HuncherOutside: I have buried it deep in the earth, and upon it built a house!
translated_text: HuncherOutside: I have buried it deep in the earth, and upon it built a house!

original_text: HuncherOutside: You must obey this house!
translated_text: HuncherOutside: You must obey this house!

original_text: HuncherOutside: [shake=.02]Accept it! You're freezing in the brambles tonight![/shake]
translated_text: HuncherOutside: [shake=.02]Accept it! You're freezing in the brambles tonight![/shake]

translated_text: Adina: There was something in that house. If I was just quick enough...

original_text: Adina: Need something special for this.
translated_text: Adina: Need something special for this.

original_text: Adina: Oh god, I have to get back into that house.
translated_text: Adina: Oh god, I have to get back into that house.

original_text: Adina: This is the worst Longest Night ever.
translated_text: Adina: This is the worst Longest Night ever.

translated_text: HuncherInside: When you're out there tonight, freezing,

original_text: HuncherInside: will you look for my ring?
translated_text: HuncherInside: will you look for my ring?

original_text: HuncherInside: Once something's down in the brambles I can never see it.
translated_text: HuncherInside: Once something's down in the brambles I can never see it.

translated_text: HuncherKid: I found your ring last week.

original_text: HuncherInside: It's my second most prized possession.
translated_text: HuncherInside: It's my second most prized possession.

original_text: HuncherInside: I keep the most prized in a shrine, so precious is it to me.
translated_text: HuncherInside: I keep the most prized in a shrine, so precious is it to me.

original_text: HuncherInside: And so painful. We have to keep the precious and painful close.
translated_text: HuncherInside: And so painful. We have to keep the precious and painful close.

translated_text: Adina: I feel like we keep getting off-track here.

translated_text: HuncherInside: I can smell the Forest God's blessing on you.

original_text: HuncherInside: If you knew anything you'd wash until it came off with your skin.
translated_text: HuncherInside: If you knew anything you'd wash until it came off with your skin.

original_text: HuncherInside: When you leave, you're going down into the brambles like all the others.
translated_text: HuncherInside: When you leave, you're going down into the brambles like all the others.

original_text: HuncherInside: When I have to go outside to fix the weather
translated_text: HuncherInside: When I have to go outside to fix the weather

original_text: HuncherInside: because the weathervane got knocked around, AGAIN...
translated_text: HuncherInside: because the weathervane got knocked around, AGAIN...

original_text: HuncherKid: It's a really stupid system you have going there.
translated_text: HuncherKid: It's a really stupid system you have going there.

original_text: HuncherInside: ...when I get out to do that
translated_text: HuncherInside: ...when I get out to do that

translated_text: HuncherInside: I'll look out on the hollow, and nothing will be stirring.

original_text: HuncherInside: And that will be what happened to you.
translated_text: HuncherInside: And that will be what happened to you.

translated_text: Adina: Why don't you just kill me now, then?

translated_text: HuncherInside: I think you know the answer. You just showed up.

original_text: HuncherInside: Ugh, we all just show up.
translated_text: HuncherInside: Ugh, we all just show up.

original_text: HuncherInside: But you won't have to worry about that.
translated_text: HuncherInside: But you won't have to worry about that.

translated_text: [[Actually, I need to get to the Frozen Lake.|NeedFrozenLake]]

original_text: HuncherInside: Oh, I'll get specific with you, kid.
translated_text: HuncherInside: Oh, I'll get specific with you, kid.

original_text: HuncherInside: I'm going to bury your pieces in a lonely hollow.
translated_text: HuncherInside: I'm going to bury your pieces in a lonely hollow.

original_text: HuncherInside: Not even bury them! I didn't bury the last one.
translated_text: HuncherInside: Not even bury them! I didn't bury the last one.

original_text: HuncherInside: Your family will never find you.
translated_text: HuncherInside: Your family will never find you.

translated_text: [[*AHEM.* I need to get to the Frozen Lake.|NeedFrozenLake]]

original_text: HuncherInside: This is the dynamic of everything.
translated_text: HuncherInside: This is the dynamic of everything.

original_text: HuncherInside: They didn't even give you a name back at the sawmill, did they, kid?
translated_text: HuncherInside: They didn't even give you a name back at the sawmill, did they, kid?

original_text: HuncherKid: Excuse me, the full name was Sawmill Kid.
translated_text: HuncherKid: Excuse me, the full name was Sawmill Kid.

original_text: HuncherInside: Well, now you're just kid.
translated_text: HuncherInside: Well, now you're just kid.

original_text: HuncherInside: You never realize how little and how much you need a name
translated_text: HuncherInside: You never realize how little and how much you need a name

original_text: HuncherInside: until they refuse you yours.
translated_text: HuncherInside: until they refuse you yours.

original_text: Adina: I'm sorry to keep steering us back to this,
translated_text: Adina: I'm sorry to keep steering us back to this,

original_text: Adina: but I must reach the Frozen Lake.
translated_text: Adina: but I must reach the Frozen Lake.

original_text: Adina: I'm an astronomer. Former apprentice.
translated_text: Adina: I'm an astronomer. Former apprentice.

original_text: Adinda: First in my observatory, actually.
translated_text: Adinda: First in my observatory, actually.

original_text: HuncherInside: Oh honey, all of those stars in your head.
translated_text: HuncherInside: Oh honey, all of those stars in your head.

original_text: HuncherInside: They will go out like candles tonight.
translated_text: HuncherInside: They will go out like candles tonight.

original_text: HuncherInside: The Forest God isn't really a god.
translated_text: HuncherInside: The Forest God isn't really a god.

original_text: HuncherInside: I am twice their size.
translated_text: HuncherInside: I am twice their size.

original_text: HuncherInside: I am twice as real.
translated_text: HuncherInside: I am twice as real.

original_text: HuncherInside: Honestly, whoever you are, even you're twice as real as they are.
translated_text: HuncherInside: Honestly, whoever you are, even you're twice as real as they are.

original_text: HuncherInside: A ridiculous name. You named yourself. I can tell.
translated_text: HuncherInside: A ridiculous name. You named yourself. I can tell.

original_text: HuncherInside: Now, what would make a little girl change her last name?
translated_text: HuncherInside: Now, what would make a little girl change her last name?

original_text: HuncherInside: You don't know a thing about it. I came from somewhere.
translated_text: HuncherInside: You don't know a thing about it. I came from somewhere.

original_text: HuncherInside: As did the woman before me.
translated_text: HuncherInside: As did the woman before me.

original_text: HuncherInside: And we found the cabin, and I fed the oven.
translated_text: HuncherInside: And we found the cabin, and I fed the oven.

original_text: HuncherInside: And we survived, and then I survived.
translated_text: HuncherInside: And we survived, and then I survived.

original_text: HuncherInside: And the quarrel with the Forest God went on for centuries.
translated_text: HuncherInside: And the quarrel with the Forest God went on for centuries.

original_text: HuncherInside: Until it ended. Quite recently.
translated_text: HuncherInside: Until it ended. Quite recently.

original_text: HuncherInside: I swear if I wasn't physically present in here she'd talk about anything.
translated_text: HuncherInside: I swear if I wasn't physically present in here she'd talk about anything.

original_text: HuncherInside: What is a witch? You mean the women in the woods?
translated_text: HuncherInside: What is a witch? You mean the women in the woods?

original_text: HuncherInside: A man in the woods is a hermit or a woodsman or a huntsman.
translated_text: HuncherInside: A man in the woods is a hermit or a woodsman or a huntsman.

original_text: HuncherInside: They didn't have a name for women who weren't where they should be.
translated_text: HuncherInside: They didn't have a name for women who weren't where they should be.

original_text: HuncherInside: So they stole a name they feared and hated
translated_text: HuncherInside: So they stole a name they feared and hated

original_text: HuncherInside: and pressed it onto us.
translated_text: HuncherInside: and pressed it onto us.

original_text: HuncherKid: Onto you. The word they use for girls like me is "kidnapped".
translated_text: HuncherKid: Onto you. The word they use for girls like me is "kidnapped".

original_text: HuncherInside: This one. Every day, I swear.
translated_text: HuncherInside: This one. Every day, I swear.

original_text: Adina: Why not send her back where she came from?
translated_text: Adina: Why not send her back where she came from?

original_text: HuncherInside: That is the one question to which I have no answer.
translated_text: HuncherInside: That is the one question to which I have no answer.

original_text: HuncherInside: I know you wanted to live
translated_text: HuncherInside: I know you wanted to live

original_text: HuncherInside: But I've taken that future from you
translated_text: HuncherInside: But I've taken that future from you

original_text: HuncherInside: And you can't take it back.
translated_text: HuncherInside: And you can't take it back.

original_text: HuncherOutside: Girl, what have you done?
translated_text: HuncherOutside: Girl, what have you done?

original_text: HuncherOutside: It wasn't me! It was this place!
translated_text: HuncherOutside: It wasn't me! It was this place!

original_text: HuncherSisterGhost: [wave][size=.85]It was the oven. It was what you became.[/all]
translated_text: HuncherSisterGhost: [wave][size=.85]It was the oven. It was what you became.[/all]

original_text: HuncherOutside: I didn't get to choose what happened to me!
translated_text: HuncherOutside: I didn't get to choose what happened to me!

original_text: HuncherSisterGhost: [wave][size=.85]I was so cold. I was so afraid.[/all]
translated_text: HuncherSisterGhost: [wave][size=.85]I was so cold. I was so afraid.[/all]

original_text: Adina: What is this? Who are you?
translated_text: Adina: What is this? Who are you?

original_text: HuncherOutside: Don't you dare speak, you waste of a girl.
translated_text: HuncherOutside: Don't you dare speak, you waste of a girl.

original_text: HuncherSisterGhost: [wave][size=.85]I was her twin! We fled into the woods, identical in all things[/all]
translated_text: HuncherSisterGhost: [wave][size=.85]I was her twin! We fled into the woods, identical in all things[/all]

original_text: HuncherSisterGhost: [wave][size=.85]When she pulled my body from the water[/all]
translated_text: HuncherSisterGhost: [wave][size=.85]When she pulled my body from the water[/all]

original_text: HuncherSisterGhost: [wave][size=.85]the only part of me she kept[/all]
translated_text: HuncherSisterGhost: [wave][size=.85]the only part of me she kept[/all]

original_text: HuncherOutside: I've kept it close to me all down the centuries.
translated_text: HuncherOutside: I've kept it close to me all down the centuries.

original_text: HuncherSisterGhost: [wave][size=.85]I believed in some idea of you...[/all]
translated_text: HuncherSisterGhost: [wave][size=.85]I believed in some idea of you...[/all]

original_text: HuncherSisterGhost: [wave][size=.85]that is as long dead as i am now.[/all]
translated_text: HuncherSisterGhost: [wave][size=.85]that is as long dead as i am now.[/all]

original_text: Adina: Oh my god. I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry for this.
translated_text: Adina: Oh my god. I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry for this.

original_text: Adina: I'm sorry!!! I never meant to-
translated_text: Adina: I'm sorry!!! I never meant to-

original_text: Mae: What is this story about?
translated_text: Mae: What is this story about?

original_text: Granddad: What do you want it to be about?
translated_text: Granddad: What do you want it to be about?

original_text: Mae: If I get to choose what it's about, it's not about anything.
translated_text: Mae: If I get to choose what it's about, it's not about anything.

original_text: Granddad: Huh. That's quite a statement.
translated_text: Granddad: Huh. That's quite a statement.

original_text: Granddad: Well you came up with that plan to rob banks
translated_text: Granddad: Well you came up with that plan to rob banks

original_text: Granddad: so clearly you're onto something.
translated_text: Granddad: so clearly you're onto something.

original_text: Mae: I want to know what this is about.
translated_text: Mae: I want to know what this is about.

original_text: Granddad: I think you have to figure that out on your own.
translated_text: Granddad: I think you have to figure that out on your own.

original_text: Adina: I can get you out of here.
translated_text: Adina: I can get you out of here.

original_text: HuncherKid: You can't even get yourself out of here.
translated_text: HuncherKid: You can't even get yourself out of here.

original_text: HuncherKid: I can barely get out of the attic
translated_text: HuncherKid: I can barely get out of the attic

original_text: HuncherKid: and away from that extremely creepy shrine.
translated_text: HuncherKid: and away from that extremely creepy shrine.

original_text: Adina: It's not safe for you here.
translated_text: Adina: It's not safe for you here.

original_text: HuncherKid: Did you know, I made that poison and she never even thanked me?
translated_text: HuncherKid: Did you know, I made that poison and she never even thanked me?

original_text: HuncherKid: She'll take all the credit for it!
translated_text: HuncherKid: She'll take all the credit for it!

original_text: HuncherKid: Murdering a god isn't something you want to let someone else take credit for.
translated_text: HuncherKid: Murdering a god isn't something you want to let someone else take credit for.

original_text: HuncherKid: Nobody who would know I'm gone is anyone I'd want to find me.
translated_text: HuncherKid: Nobody who would know I'm gone is anyone I'd want to find me.

original_text: HuncherKid: Get away if you can.
translated_text: HuncherKid: Get away if you can.

original_text: Adina: Should probably check that house first.
translated_text: Adina: Should probably check that house first.

original_text: Adina: Some of that weird snow is way up in the trees.
translated_text: Adina: Some of that weird snow is way up in the trees.
